<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1057" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1057">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.112 Er 4/3.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister in temporary charge of the
                                    Embassy at Constantinople</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-28"><hi rend="italic">November 28,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The embassy is instructed to report what action has been taken on
                            Department’s telegram of November 1, 1910, also to investigate the
                            reported arrest of Erickson at Monastir on the 20th ultimo and to take
                            appropriate action.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>